{"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Class","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticMutex"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"StaticMutex","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"StaticMutex","externalID":"s:4GLib11StaticMutexC","symbolKind":"class"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" works like a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol"]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"StaticMutex","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Prior to GLib 2.32, GStaticMutex had the significant advantage","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that it doesn’t need to be created at run-time, but can be defined","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"at compile-time. Since 2.32, ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","isActive":true},{"text":" can be statically allocated","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as well, and GStaticMutex has been deprecated."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Here is a version of our ","type":"text"},{"code":"give_me_next_number()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" example using","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a GStaticMutex:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["  int","  give_me_next_number (void)","  {","    static int current_number = 0;","    int ret_val;","    static GStaticMutex mutex = G_STATIC_MUTEX_INIT;","","    g_static_mutex_lock (&mutex);","    ret_val = current_number = calc_next_number (current_number);","    g_static_mutex_unlock (&mutex);","","    return ret_val;","  }"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Sometimes you would like to dynamically create a mutex. If you don’t"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"want to require prior calling to "},{"code":"g_thread_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", because your code"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"should also be usable in non-threaded programs, you are not able to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_mutex_new()"},{"type":"text","text":" and thus "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", as that requires a prior call to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"text":". In these cases you can also use a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It must be initialized with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" before using it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and freed with with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_free()"},{"type":"text","text":" when not needed anymore to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"free up any allocated resources."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Even though ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is not opaque, it should only be used with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the following functions, as it is defined differently on different"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"platforms.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"All of the g_static_mutex_* functions apart from","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_static_mutex_get_mutex()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" can also be used even if ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_thread_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"has not yet been called. Then they do nothing, apart from","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_trylock()"},{"type":"text","text":" which does nothing but returning "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All of the g_static_mutex_* functions are actually macros. Apart from"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"taking their addresses, you can however use them as if they were"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"functions.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as an owner of an underlying "},{"code":"GStaticMutex","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","type":"reference"},{"text":" as a strong reference or owner of a ","type":"text"},{"code":"GStaticMutex","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" (instead of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStaticMutex"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note"}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(_:)-30gyb","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(_:)-5ndjt","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(_:)-6lhvr","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(_:)-7apmz","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(_:)-8rbuv","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(opaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(raw:)-1nyk4","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(raw:)-5it8v","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(retaining:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(retainingCPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(retainingOpaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(retainingRaw:)-290rd","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(retainingRaw:)-8drmn"]